properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 1 at 4:40PM EST until February 3 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and waves
5 to 8 feet expected.

* WHERE...Manitou Island to Point Isabelle MI, Point Isabelle to
Lower Entrance of Portage Canal MI, Lower Entrance of Portage
Canal To Huron Islands MI Including Keweenaw and Huron Bays,
Huron Islands to Marquette MI and Lake Superior West of Line
from Manitou Island to Marquette MI Beyond 5NM from shore.

* WHEN...From 1 PM Sunday to 1 AM EST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM SUNDAY TO 1 AM EST MONDAY
